result.formatted_address: 38號 See Cheung St, Sai Kung, Hong Kong
result.name: Taps

reviews.text:
A must try in Saikung. 

Small coffee shop with a Japanese theme, real wooden furniture, metal utensils, and a homely, comfortable feel. 

Two tables outside - useful if with dog(s) - and more inside. Suitable for small groups. 

Bilingual menu with plenty to choose. 

Select and pay first at the counter and your order gets delivered to you. Octopus, credit cards and cash accepted. 

[I always try to pay by cash in small shops so the owners don't get hit with a transactional surcharge by the ecash people.] 

The sourdough bread with feta cheese, salmon and rocket was delicious although the coffee I ordered separately was a little too strong for my liking. 

Thought it was value for money at HK$118. Will recommend and return.

咖啡與食物的質素不錯，而且食物選擇多。攜犬的可坐店外的座位，可惜只有兩張枱，經常滿座。店員亦親切地詳細講解並推介菜單內容。

店內座位頗為擠逼，而且冷氣不足，頗為侷促。
週末休閒到西頁走走的話，可以到Taps來一個all day breakfast，它雖然店舖少少，而食物超有水準，咖啡又好味。它的沙律菜是火箭菜來的，非常新鮮。
